latestIgtvVideos.title: To me 🖤
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The thought of having no control over who sees this video is terrifying. That thought alone almost stopped me from making it. I can assure you, I didn’t make this video for attention or to gain sympathy... the last thing I wanted to do was reflect on this year at all.
I never knew I could be given as difficult a test as I was given this year. I never knew I could be so sad, I never knew I could be so confused, I never knew I could be so angry, so anxious, so unsure, so scared, so hurt. That being said, I saw no other choice but to keep going, day by day, and that showed me exactly what I was made of. I saw no other option than to trust God, for I wouldn’t use this year as a reason to be angry with Him. One day, I hope to look back at this year and see how it was the year that shaped me and changed my life for the better. One day, I hope to look back on this year and smile. You may not know how you survived this year... I don’t know how I survived this year. But we did. & I’m so proud of us. Moral of the story is, life goes on, even when you feel like it won’t.
To my family, my sister @alexandra.dej, my friends— old and new (@_michii13, @ashley_leone_, @ecomamajourney, @jennarosee__, @anthonyjohnbruno, @katherinea.l, @adinahsilva, @anaa.aangel), my IG family and supporters—
I love you and thank you for holding my hand through this year.
~This song is To Me by @alinabaraz and it’s been my anthem all year ✨

latestIgtvVideos.title: Skin Maintenance Routine Using @dermaflash
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
My Skin Maintenance Routine — Skincare products are only part of taking the utmost care of your skin. A skincare routine and a skin maintenance routine are two different routines but both go hand in hand. 
Without the proper skin maintenance routine, you may not be getting the full skincare benefits from your products. I was so lucky to have been gifted these two devices by @dermaflash and able to test them for the past few months. This video is not paid nor sponsored by Dermaflash.
I’ve been shaving my face (what is now called derma-planing) for years. Derma-planing is a form of physical exfoliation which removes any surface debris, vellus hair (aka peach fuzz) and dead skin allowing for your products to penetrate further into your skin’s barrier. While I’ve used many blades and devices to derma-plane in the past, Dermaflash has by far been the best and easiest to use!
I follow up with Dermapore with is both an extractor and infuser device. Extraction pulls stubborn sebum from deep down in your pores making them ready to receive any skincare products you apply. This is where Infuse comes in. Dermapore sends vibrations through the skin’s surface to infuse your products deep into your pores. This process results in the most lively, radiant, glowing, healthy looking skin! I may still breakout here and there, but my skin has NEVER looked or felt this amazing texture-wise. Since incorporating these devices into my routine, my pores have become virtually non existent and it shows in this video.
#skinmaintenance #dermaplaning #skinextractions #athomefacial #dermaflash #dermapore #notanad #notsponsored

latestIgtvVideos.title: Minimal Morning Skincare Routine
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
It’s been forever since I last updated you guys on my skincare routine! As a beauty influencer, I’m constantly trying and testing new products and tbh, I haven’t had a solid morning skincare routine in a while. Between the many different products, life and mascne, my skin has been seriously stressed and I’ve ultimately found that keeping it super simple & minimal has been my saving grace. I’m truly happy with this routine, it’s been working very well for me and I’ve been sticking to it for the past two months or so. In this video, I’ll also be introducing the new @origins Into The Glow brightening serum (the only serum I’m using during the day & it’s been a game changer)! This serum delivers radiant results using a vegan, multi-action formula contains a 5% Retexturizing Complex that is packed full of beneficial ingredients to give your skin the refresh it desperately needs. A blend of green coffee seed extract, AHA’s & BHA’s, and panax ginseng boosts cell turnover (my favorite process) to gently remove dead skin cells (a must), improve skin’s dullness and less visible pores resulting in overall smoother, clearer looking skin. 
I hope you guys enjoy this video! Sometimes less really is more! #ad #originspartner #radianceisreal

latestIgtvVideos.title: Super Simple Dalgona Matcha (vegan & dairy free)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
If this doesn’t just ooze Sunday afternoon then idk what does! This is the last thing I ever thought I’d attempt but I got caught in the trend trap when I saw a few people making matcha versions of this. Y’all know I’m not a coffee drinker anymore but I sure love my matcha. For those that are living under a rock (lol jk jk!), for anyone who may be unfamiliar with this latest Korean drink trend, this indulgent whipped goodness is called #dalgonamatcha (or the more popularly made #dalgonacoffee).
And yes, it tastes just as good as it looks. Please enjoy this super simple, coffee alternative, vegan friendly, dairy free version of #dalgonamatcha 🍵☕️
••INGREDIENTS•• •1 13.5 oz canned coconut milk *make sure to refrigerated overnight the night prior to making or it will not whip* (I tried three different kinds and the 365 Everyday Value organic canned coconut milk gave me the BEST results by far!)
•1 TSP of organic matcha powder
•2 TSP of vanilla syrup for sweetener (you can use any liquid sweetener of your choice or you can even boil water and sugar to make your own syrup)
•oat milk of your choice for your base
ENJOY!
Song: When You Love Somebody by @robinthicke

latestPosts.caption:
1. being “successful” and what my definition of “success” or “greatness” even looks like. I’m so grateful to have the privilege of doing what I’ve always wanted to do for a career, yet I still find myself constantly struggling with feeling behind in life, if this career path is sustainable and wanting to switch careers the moment it starts to feel too stagnant. In summation, deprogramming my mind of societal norms and the pressures of where you should be/what you should have by 30.

2. whether or not, I want to be a mom. This is such a loaded one but the decision truly causes me so much stress and anxiety especially being in my 30s. May be a hot take but I don’t think the subject gets thought through nearly as much as it should. Though I’ve seen myself having children for as long as I can remember, I wrestle with the decision now as an adult who fully grasps how that choice would impact my life.

3. if I will ever truly fully heal from my trauma. Period. 

4. getting a handle on my ADHD and if seeking an official diagnosis is worth all the money if it ultimately does not change the fact that I have it (nor will I want to take medication for it).

5. if I will ever learn to genuinely love some of my natural features that I’m still insecure about to this day. My under eyes and lips are two areas I have always struggled with. I’ve held off on getting my lips redone for over 6 years in an attempt to learn to accept them as they are, but now in my 30s, the desire to change both my lips and under eyes has only grown.

I could honestly go on 😅 but I felt this was a refreshing and raw shift from the highlight reel that is social media. My 30s has genuinely been my favorite and best chapter of my life thus far but the horrors do indeed persist lol. I fear we may never rid ourselves of worry… as is life 🤷🏻‍♀️🥹
I would love to hear from you in the comments if you relate to any of these 🫶🏼🫂✨
